  "prompt": "How a B.Tech CSE can get a job at ISRO?",
  "response": "Getting a job at the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) as a B.Tech in Computer Science Engineering (CSE) graduate involves several steps and thorough preparation. Here\u2019s a detailed guide:\n\n### 1. Understand the Requirements:\n\nISRO primarily recruits engineers through the **ISRO Centralised Recruitment Board (ICRB)**. The typical entry-level position for engineers is **Scientist/Engineer 'SC'**.\n\n### 2. Eligibility Criteria:\n\n- **Educational Qualification**: A B.Tech degree in Computer Science Engineering with at least 65% marks or a CGPA of 6.84 on a scale of 10.\n- **Age Limit**: Generally, the maximum age limit is 35 years. Age relaxation is applicable for reserved categories.\n\n### 3. Keep an Eye on Recruitment Notifications:\n\nISRO regularly posts recruitment notifications on its official website and other major employment portals. These notifications include details about eligibility, application procedures, and exam dates.\n\n### 4. Application Process:\n\n- **Online Application**: Apply through the official ISRO website. Fill out the application form accurately.\n- **Application Fee**: Pay the application fee if required. Fee details will be mentioned in the notification.\n\n### 5. Preparation for Written Test:\n\nISRO conducts a written examination to shortlist candidates. The test may cover topics from:\n- Your specific branch of engineering (CSE subjects: Data Structures, Algorithms, Operating Systems, Database Management, Network Security, etc.)\n- General aptitude, including logical reasoning, quantitative aptitude, and basic mathematics.\n\n### 6. Written Examination:\n\nThe examination typically comprises objective-type questions. Focus on:\n- Understanding the fundamental concepts of computer science.\n- Solving previous years\u2019 question papers.\n- Practicing mock tests to improve speed and accuracy.\n\n### 7. Interview Process:\n\n- **Shortlisting**: Candidates who qualify in the written test are shortlisted for an interview.\n- **Technical Interview**: Expect questions on core CSE subjects, projects you have worked on, and possibly some programming problems.\n- **HR Interview**: Assess your soft skills, teamwork capabilities, and motivation to work at ISRO.\n\n### 8. Documentation and Background Check:\n\nEnsure all your educational and identification documents are in order. ISRO will verify your credentials.\n\n### 9. Training and Assignment:\n\nSelected candidates undergo training at ISRO centers before being assigned specific projects or roles.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Higher Education**: While a B.Tech degree is sufficient, higher qualifications like M.Tech or relevant certifications can enhance your profile.\n- **Research Experience**: Engaging in research projects or internships related to space technology or computing can be beneficial.\n- **Networking**: Attend conferences, workshops, and seminars related to aerospace and computing to make valuable connections.\n- **Stay Updated**: Continuously update your knowledge about ISRO\u2019s projects, missions, and technology advancements.\n\n### Conclusion:\n\nPersistence, diligent preparation, and a genuine passion for space technology are key to securing a position at ISRO. With the right qualifications and dedication, a B.Tech CSE graduate can effectively contribute to India's premier space research organization.",
